[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/jacoby_2nt_splinters"]
[Student "S"]
{With opening hand and 4-card \S support this is an ideal Jacoby 2NT response. Partner says 3NT.  

North has some extra strength and a 5-card \S suit. This is the point in the bidding where you would make a control bid, showing an Ace. Well, you would if you actually had an Ace. The way you indicate your lack of a control is to just return the the agreed trump suit. So you bid 4\S and partner passes.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
[Deal "E:AQJT85.K4.84.AT3 42.9653.AT73.Q52 K973.J7.KQ65.KJ8 6.AQT82.J92.9764"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "4S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
1S pass 2NT pass 3S pass 4S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "ddcdc7442e99122c261560f3d182229728e1c8b51b408932ee4f7ced75e1f2bd"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/jacoby_2nt_splinters"]
[Student "S"]
{You show an above minimum hand with 6 trumps by bidding 3\S. Partner bids 4\S. What do you say next? 

Partner would have shown a red Ace if he had one. Since he doesn't have one, all thoughts of slam are off. You pass.}

